PIC AND STUDENT WERE ON LOCAL INSTRUCTIONAL FLIGHT. PIC CALLED ON UNICOM AND 
SAID HE WOULD SHOW BYSTANDERS 'GREASY SIDE OF AIRCRAFT.' HE BUZZED RUNWAY AT A 
LOW ALTITUDE, EXECUTED AN AILERON ROLL WHICH WAS SCOOPED OUT, AND 
IMPACTED THE GROUND BESIDE THE RUNWAY. SON OF FBO SAID PIC PERFORMED ROLL 
PREVIOUS DAY IN THE SAME AIRCRAFT, PULLED BACK ON CONTROL YOKE WHEN 
INVERTED, AND LOST ABOUT 500 FEET ALTITUDE. NO RECORD WAS FOUND THAT PIC 
HAD RECEIVED AEROBATIC TRAINING BUT HAD DISCUSSED MANEUVER WITH 
OTHER PILOTS. 
